title Sala-broadcast and the Glowphone — two grounded studies, hardware facts researched and cited
prompt Keaton asked for something for Sala like Asciinema meets WebSockets meets Twitch meets Realidream meets Mycelium meets Lattice meets Pool meets the Cursor-iOS app -- a way to broadcast/livestream a promoting mobile session; and to fuse the self-hosted Minisforum-compute dream with the Mantrapod dream into a Glowphone on the freest-firmware open ARM chips + mobile AI silicon, with a durable low-blue-light true-black display, fusing Glow OS + Urbit + Rye OS with GrapheneOS or the best Android alternative, or another strategy for that advanced firmware. Write in Quin Radiant Style following the compass, audit for integrity in Civic Style, commit push merge.
think walked the compass rather than free-associating: read the Mantrapod venture pitch, the Minisforum local-forge essay, the mesh-inference study, and money-close-to-home first, so both writings grow from foundations already seated rather than inventing.
think found the unifying idea for Sala-broadcast before writing: a livestream is a fold over a signed, ordered log -- exactly this tree's own spine. Asciinema already proves a session is a replayable event log, not a video; Twitch's live-audience/chat/VOD maps to Comlink subscriptions + folded signed facts + the Mantra log at rest; WebSockets is just the transport role Comlink plays; Mycelium (Comlink's ordering aspect) is the ordered-stream seam, now with a concrete motivation. Almost nothing is new machinery -- named that plainly.
think refused to fake the hardware answer for the Glowphone -- ran real web research (dated July 2026, cited) and found a genuine three-way tension: firmware freedom points to Rockchip mainline (open BL31, Rocket NPU) or mainline-Qualcomm; hardened security points to GrapheneOS which is Pixel-only (closed firmware, MTE) -- the irony that the most hardened phone runs the least-free silicon; open on-device AI points to AMD Strix Halo (open amdxdna, ROCm 7, fwupd) which is a mini-PC not a phone. No device is all three.
think resolved the fork the way the seed's own instinct pointed: a two-body design -- a firmware-free calm client in the hand (Rockchip-class/mainline-Qualcomm), the open-AI AMD forge at home (the Minisforum), joined by the sovereign Comlink/mesh seam. This is the Mantrapod-plus-Minisforum fusion made honest: firmware freedom in the carried body, open AI in the home body, neither compromising for the other. Named the Glowphone a sibling to the Mantrapod (glowing/connected vs reflective/forgetting), not a replacement.
think named both OS paths with their real trades (mainline/postmarketOS freest-firmware but security-ours-to-build; GrapheneOS-on-Pixel hardest-security but least-free silicon and Android-underneath), recommended leading with Path A for the Glowphone's own identity while keeping Path B for hardened-threat-model users -- and answered the advanced-firmware-strategy question honestly: own the seam nothing can route around, not a miracle chip that does not exist.
think audited both writings in Civic Style explicitly, as its own section in each: named the outcome wanted, what the reward measures (verifiable broadcast served / longevity + sovereignty, never attention captured or data harvested), and that the incentive and ethic point the same way. Marked every claim design-register (Two Rooms), dated and cited every hardware fact, and thanked every studied source (Asciinema, iroh/n0, Rockchip mainline, AMD, GrapheneOS/CalyxOS/DivestOS) in the gratitude way with nothing copied.
obs kept placeholder and honesty discipline: no invented benchmark numbers, the modest-latency and OLED-burn-in caveats named rather than hidden, and the largest cost of the recommended path (Path A's security gap vs GrapheneOS) stated as its own line rather than buried.
