recommend check-in -- both are horizon studies that touch procurement (the Glowphone needs a real machine and budget) and gate behind Pool P0 (Sala-broadcast). Worth Keaton's read on whether either graduates toward a lap -- Sala-broadcast's B0 (session-as-log) is small and could ride the Pool P0 sitting; the Glowphone is a longer procurement horizon whose next honest step is a dedicated-machine decision, not code.
